 Port Elizabeth - Eastern Cape SAPS Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant General Liziwe Ntshinga, expressed her condolences to the family of an eight-year-old scholar, who died in a freak accident while playing at his school earlier on Wednesday. "It is alleged that between 12:20 and 12:30, Luhavan Potgieter was playing with his friends on the school grounds near concrete water pipes," said police spokesperson, W/O Alwin Labans. "The children were playing on and inside the pipes when he was fatally injured." W/O Labans said that police have opened an inquest docket for investigation. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  